article.headline: New Hampshire 101, Suffolk 50
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. -- Guards Eric Gilchrese scored 21 points and Tyrece Gibbs added 18 to lead New Hampshire to a 101-50 victory over Suffolk on Sunday. The 51-point margin is the largest for the Wildcats since records were available starting with the 1941-42 season. Gilchrese hit 7 of 10 shots, including a career-high six 3-pointers. Gibbs was 7 of 11 from the field. New Hampshire scored 22 straight points to open the game before Suffolk hit its first basket with 11:46 to go in the first half. The Rams cut the deficit to 27-13, but the Wildcats closed the half with a 12-3 run for a 50-27 lead. A 17-2 New Hampshire run made it 67-31. Mario Massimino was the high scorer for Suffolk with 16 points and Allan Ray added 11 points.
